-# Locals: casual_name
- casual_name = local_assigns.fetch(:casual_name)
- one_thing_book_url = "https://www.amazon.com/ONE-Thing-Surprisingly-Extraordinary-Results/dp/1885167776"

.alert.alert-light.border.mb-0
  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Goal of this page
  %p.mb-3
    Answer, for #{casual_name}'s clarity:
    %em what is the one thing that I can do such that by doing it, makes everything else either easier or unnecessary
    — then do that thing. Clarity leads to flow, which leads to thriving.

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Context
  = render 'shared/maap/definition'
  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 The One Thing
  %p.mb-3
    This page is named after the focusing question from
    = link_to "The One Thing", one_thing_book_url, target: "_blank", rel: "noopener noreferrer"
    by Gary Keller and Jay Papasan. The book asks:
    %em="\"What's the ONE Thing I can do such that by doing it everything else will be easier or unnecessary?\""
    My One Thing is meant to be that answer for #{casual_name}'s clarity — which leads to flow — which leads to thriving.

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Specifics of this page
  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 What you see first
  %ul.mb-3
    %li
      %strong The question
      — the top clarity need for #{casual_name} this week.
    %li
      %strong The next action
      — the concrete step to take so that need gets clearer.
    %li
      %strong Supporting items
      — linked details under the top priority when they help you act.

  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 How we choose the one thing
  %p.mb-0
    Expand
    %strong How we choose the one thing
    below the carousel for the priority order and tie-break rules. Overview and Detailed tabs add health and history when you need more context — start here when you only need what to do next.
